<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="57" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,430,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57">Material examined.</emphasis>
<number box="[437,472,151,175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" value="13.0">13</number>
, Maoershan, Xing'an county, Guangxi, 
<date box="[918,1074,151,175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" value="1921-09">
<number box="[918,946,151,175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" value="21.0">21</number>
September
</date>
, 
<number box="[1085,1143,151,175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" value="2011.0">2011</number>
, collected by Bian Xun. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,330,187,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57">Discussion.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Liu" box="[337,533,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" refString="Liu X. - W. &amp; Yin H. - S. (2002) Two new species of Gryllacridinae from China (Orthoptera: Stenopelmatidae). Zoological Research, 23 (5), 417 - 418." type="journal article" year="2002">
Liu &amp; Yin (
<number box="[466,525,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[654,882,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Eremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvospinus">
<emphasis box="[654,882,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="57">Eremus parvospinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[946,994,189,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57">type</typeStatus>
specimen is only 
<specimenCount box="[1195,1292,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" type="female">
<number box="[1195,1209,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" value="1.0">1</number>
female
</specimenCount>
and the 
<typeStatus box="[1387,1435,189,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57">type</typeStatus>
locality is Maoershan in Guangxi. Now we examined 
<specimenCount box="[754,829,223,247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" type="male">
<number box="[754,768,223,247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" value="1.0">1</number>
male
</specimenCount>
specimen of the species which was collected from the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,261,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57">type</typeStatus>
locality. The subgenital plate of male without styli, which is characteristic of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1193,1319,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Apotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1193,1319,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="57">Apotrechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We think it should belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[480,607,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Apotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[480,607,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="57">Apotrechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male is described for the first time.
</paragraph>
